Femi Fani-Kayode, a chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, has thanked President Muhammadu Buhari for allegedly concluding plans to ensure the country’s breakup. According to the former Aviation Minister, if the information he has received concerning the President’s plan is anything to go by, then there is no hope for Nigeria’s unity. Fani-Kayode, an ardent critic of the present administration, stated this in a tweet on Friday, adding that Nigeria may break into “two or five pieces.” He said, “The things that I am hearing about @MBuhari’s plans leaves me with only one conclusion: by the time this dance is over Nigeria is likely to have broken into between two to five pieces. “Thanks to our President, a few years from now we may not have a Nigeria left!” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.